                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6">Information Collection</h2>
                <p>“Personally Identifiable Information” means any information that either on its own or when combined with certain other information can identify an individual and for the purpose of this Privacy Policy usually limited to Your mobile phone number or address book contact numbers. JVR may obtain the following types of information from or concerning You or Your mobile device, which may include personal information that can be used to identify You as specified below:</p>

                <p><strong>User Provided Information:</strong> You provide certain Personally Identifiable Information, such as Your mobile phone number, name and mobile device information to JVR when choosing to participate in the use of the JVR application, such as registering as a user, messaging other JVR users, uploading images. In order to provide the JVR service, JVR shall periodically access Your address book or contact list on Your mobile phone to locate the mobile phone numbers of other JVR users. Seen or not seen a message is reported to JVR and is visible to the admin. JVR may receive data whenever You connect with an application or site through JVR. This may include date and time You visit the site, the web address, IP address information, browser and if You are logged into JVR and Your authentication tokens used on such sites. Your authentication tokens may be saved on the server for the sole purpose of seamless posting to the same site by You in the future through JVR. JVR does not collect emails, addresses or other contact information from its users’ mobile address book other than mobile phone numbers and names associated with such mobile phone numbers.</p>

                <p>The JVR mobile application will associate whatever name the JVR user has assigned to the mobile telephone number in his/her mobile address book. As a result, if You have Your friend’s mobile phone number associated with the name “Doctor” or “Electrician” in Your mobile address book, that’s the name that will appear for that mobile phone number in Your JVR list of contacts. We do not collect location data, but at times users may voluntarily share their location with other users via the JVR application. Any profile image updates posted a user is saved in our servers. JVR may retain date and time stamp information associated with successfully delivered messages and the mobile phone numbers involved in the messages, as well as any other information which JVR is legally compelled to collect in accordance with retention policies applicable under Indian law.</p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6">Use of Information</h2>
